    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-25T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-25T10:00:00-05:00" n="86"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94Advisory Committee/3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-25T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 25, 1933—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 25—11:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>128. My 127, February 24, 9 p.m.<note n="33" xml:id="d86fn33">Not printed.</note>
                    The following letter dated February 25th addressed to the Secretary of State by
                    Drummond has just been received: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I have the honor to inform you that the Assembly of the League of
                            Nations adopted on the 24th February the resolution of which the <pb
                                facs="0211" n="115" xml:id="pg_115"/> text is enclosed herewith (see
                            Gilbert’s telegram No. 60, February 24, 7 p.m.).<note n="35"
                                xml:id="d86fn35">Telegram not printed; text of resolution printed,
                                    <ref target="#pg_113">p. 113</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>The Advisory Committee set up under the terms of this resolution held a
                            meeting today. In accordance with the instructions of the Assembly it
                            requested me to convey to your Government an invitation to cooperate in
                            its work.</p>
                        <p>I need not say that the committee attachés great importance to the
                            cooperation of your Government and earnestly hopes that it will be able
                            to accept this invitation.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
